---
title: Veggie Chorizo Tacos with Kiwi Salsa and Lime Crema
description: It’s time to get your taco on: veggie crumbles with chorizo spices are the centerpiece of these tortillas, giving you smokiness, savoriness, and a slightly spicy kick, too. There’s also a kiwi and tomato salsa to keep things bright, tangy, and a sassy. Just drizzle a bit of zesty lime crema over it all, and you’ve got a devilishly good combo of textures and flavors.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5a99c9c330006c755507dc12-121e25cf.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/seitan-tacos-el-diablo-5a99c9c330006c755507dc12-cd30b49a.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/veggie-chorizo-tacos-5a99c9c330006c755507dc12
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1080 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Mince a few
slices until you have 3 TBSP minced onion. Core and seed @poblano pepper{1}, then
thinly slice. Core and seed @roma tomato{1}, then cut into ¼-inch cubes. Peel
@kiwi{2} and cut into ¼-inch cubes. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest a big
pinch of zest from @lime{1}, then cut lime into wedges.

Combine tomato, minced onion, kiwis, a squeeze of lime juice, and half the cilantro
in a #small bowl{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and more lime juice (to taste).
Set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add poblano and sliced onion. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook, tossing, until softened and slightly charred, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add @veggie chorizo crumbles{8%ounce} and another drizzle of oil to pan and toss to
combine. Season with salt and pepper. Cook until crumbles are warmed through and
starting to brown, about ~{5%minutes}. Reduce heat to low to keep warm, stirring
occasionally.

In another small bowl, combine lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and
@sour cream{4%tablespoon}. Season with salt, pepper, and more lime juice (to
taste). Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in a moist #paper towel{} and microwave on high
until warm, about ~{30%seconds}.

Fill tortillas with crumble mixture, then top with kiwi salsa and dollop with
lime crema. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges
on the side for squeezing over.